quran[31]{c,v,t,f}:
  74,40,"In Gardens (Paradise) they will ask one another,"
  74,41,"About Al-Mujrimûn (polytheists, criminals, disbelievers), (And they will say to them):"
  74,42,""
  75,37,"Was he not a Nutfah (mixed male and female sexual discharge) of semen emitted (poured forth)?"
  75,38,"Then he became an ‘Alaqah (a clot); then (Allâh) shaped and fashioned (him) in due proportion.{1}",footnotes:1:{75:38} See the footnote of {22:5}.
  75,39,"And made of him two sexes, male and female."
  76,31,"He will admit to His Mercy whom He wills and as for the Zâlimûn - (polytheists, wrong-doers) He has prepared a painful torment."
  77,28,"Woe that Day to the deniers (of the Day of Resurrection)!"
  77,29,"(It will be said to the disbelievers): "
  77,30,""
  78,25,"Except boiling water, and dirty wound discharges -"
  78,26,"An exact recompense (according to their evil crimes)."
  78,27,"For verily, they used not to look for a reckoning."
  79,19,""
  79,20,"Then [Mûsâ (Moses)] showed him the great sign (miracles)."
  79,21,"But [Fir‘aun (Pharaoh)] belied and disobeyed."
  80,16,"Honourable and obedient."
  80,17,"Be cursed (the disbelieving) man! How ungrateful he is!"
  80,18,"From what thing did He create him?"
  81,13,"And when Paradise is brought near."
  81,14,"(Then) every person will know what he has brought (of good and evil)."
  81,15,"So verily, I swear by the planets that recede (i.e. disappear during the day and appear during the night)."
  82,7,"Who created you, fashioned you perfectly, and gave you due proportion."
  82,8,"In whatever form He willed, He put you together."
  82,9,"Nay! But you deny Ad-Dîn (i.e. the Day of Recompense)."
  83,4,"Do they not think that they will be resurrected (for reckoning),"
  83,5,"On a Great Day?"
  83,6,"The Day when (all) mankind will stand before the Lord of the ‘Âlamîn (mankind, jinn and all that exists)?"
  84,1,"When the heaven is split asunder,"
  84,2,"And listens to and obeys its Lord - and it must do so."
  84,3,"And when the earth is stretched forth,"